{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 160°C.","Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in almonds and hazelnuts. Transfer to a baking tray, add garlic and set aside.","Place water in mixing bowl then place Varoma dish into position. Weigh in asparagus and drizzle with 20 g olive oil. Sprinkle ½ tsp paprika, ¼ tsp salt and 1 pinch pepper over asparagus then mix well to coat. Cover Varoma and steam <b>15-20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> until asparagus is cooked. Meanwhile, roast nuts and garlic for 10 minutes (160°C). Leave to cool then peel garlic. Once asparagus is cooked, set covered Varoma aside to keep warm. Discard cooking water.","Place reserved roasted nuts in mixing bowl then grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place reserved peeled garlic, preserved peppers, tomatoes and 20 g reserved oil from peppers in mixing bowl then blend <b>10 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides and lid of mixing bowl with spatula then heat <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add reserved ground nuts, chilli (if using), vinegar, 1 tsp paprika, ½ tsp salt and 1 pinch pepper then blend <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b><strong>-9, increasing speed gradually<\/strong>.","Transfer asparagus to a serving dish and serve warm with romesco sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["30 g blanched almonds","25 g blanched hazelnuts","1 garlic clove, unpeeled","500 g water","350 - 400 g green asparagus, woody ends removed","20 g extra virgin olive oil","1 ½ tsp sweet paprika","2 pinches ground black pepper","100 g roasted red peppers, preserved, drained, reserving 20 g oil, cut in pieces","80 g tomatoes, quartered","½ fresh red chilli, halved, deseeded (optional)","1 Tbsp red wine vinegar"]}],"id":"r341604","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-_matr_weLYk\/XZWZk8QBToI\/AAAAAAAAePI\/oI9t0PBQHr8MuSWyOqUDKyR26pTDwnggwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_g8QXuNmbOO1JIp3y.png","title":"Asparagus with Romesco Sauce","publishedAt":"2019-03-04T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"p